(17, 'Various examples of calligraphy in different languages and writing systems throughout history', 9, 13, '<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><b>Calligraphy</b>&nbsp;(from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greek_language\" title=\"Greek language\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Greek</a>: καλλιγραφία) is a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_arts\" title=\"Visual arts\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">visual art</a>&nbsp;related to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Writing\" title=\"Writing\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">writing</a>. It is the design and execution of lettering with a broad-tipped instrument,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brush\" title=\"Brush\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">brush</a>, or other writing instrument.<sup id=\"cite_ref-mediaville1996_1-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-mediaville1996-1\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup><sup class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\">:17</sup>&nbsp;A contemporary calligraphic practice can be defined as \"the art of giving form to signs in an expressive, harmonious, and skillful manner\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-mediaville1996_1-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-mediaville1996-1\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup><sup class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\">:18</sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">Modern calligraphy ranges from functional inscriptions and designs to fine-art pieces where the letters may or may not be readable.<sup id=\"cite_ref-mediaville1996_1-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-mediaville1996-1\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This citation requires a reference to the specific page or range of pages in which the material appears. (August 2016)\">page&nbsp;needed</span></a></i>]</sup>&nbsp;Classical calligraphy differs from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typography\" title=\"Typography\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">typography</a>&nbsp;and non-classical hand-lettering, though a calligrapher may practice both.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-2\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-3\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-zapf2007_4-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-zapf2007-4\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-zapf2006_5-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-zapf2006-5\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">Calligraphy continues to flourish in the forms of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wedding_invitations\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wedding invitations\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">wedding invitations</a>&nbsp;and event invitations,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Font_design\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Font design\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">font design</a>&nbsp;and typography, original hand-lettered&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logo\" title=\"Logo\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">logo</a>&nbsp;design,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Religious_art\" title=\"Religious art\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">religious art</a>, announcements,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphic_design\" title=\"Graphic design\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">graphic design</a>&nbsp;and commissioned calligraphic art, cut stone&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inscription\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Inscription\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">inscriptions</a>, and memorial&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Document\" title=\"Document\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">documents</a>. It is also used for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theatrical_property\" title=\"Theatrical property\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">props</a>&nbsp;and moving images for film and television, and also for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Testimonial\" title=\"Testimonial\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">testimonials</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birth_certificate\" title=\"Birth certificate\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">birth</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death_certificate\" title=\"Death certificate\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">death</a>&nbsp;certificates,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Map\" title=\"Map\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">maps</a>, and other written works.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-6\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calligraphy#cite_note-7\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup></p>', '2021-04-07 01:04:46', '2021-04-07 01:04:46', 1, 'Various-examples-of-calligraphy-in-different-languages-and-writing-systems-througho